   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>VIII.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>THE THANKSGIVING OF GOD'S ELECT</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>FOR GOD'S BOUNTIFUL GOODNESS</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>AND EVERLASTING LOVINGKINDNESS</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>LEADING TO CHRIST AS THE CORNERSTONE</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>FOR GOD'S BUILDING</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>In Psalm 118 we have the thanksgiving of God's elect for God's bountiful goodness and everlasting lovingkindness leading to Christ as the cornerstone for God's building.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>A. The Thanksgiving of God's Elect</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>for God's Bountiful Goodness</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>and Everlasting Lovingkindness</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Verses 1 through 21 and 27 through 29 are the thanksgiving of God's elect.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>In verse 1a the psalmist says, "Give thanks to Jehovah, for He is good."</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>This word is repeated in verse 29a.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Only God is good, as indicated by the word of the Lord Jesus to the young man in Mark 10, who had addressed Him as "Good Teacher."</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>The Lord Jesus said to him, "Why do you call Me good?</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>No one is good except One God" v. 18 . We may think that others are good, but actually besides God no one is good.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Because God is good, the psalmist said repeatedly, "His lovingkindness is forever" 118:1b, 2b, 3b, 4b, 29b .</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>B. Leading to Christ</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>as the Cornerstone for God's Building</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>According to verses 22 through 26, thanksgiving of God's elect for God's bountiful goodness and everlasting lovingkindness leads to Christ as the cornerstone for God's building.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>1.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>Christ Rejected by Israel, the Builders of God</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>In verse 22a the psalmist speaks of "the stone which the builders rejected."</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>Verse 26 indicates that the psalmist was referring not to himself but to someone else.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>In His interpretation of verses 22 and 23, the Lord Jesus revealed that He was the cornerstone rejected by the Jewish leaders as the builders of God, who, in a sense, were building something for God.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>Although Christ was the stone given to them by God, they rejected Him to such an extent that they put Him on the cross.</S>
